f=AI & Agents/relay/operational/skill/relay-skill-routing.md · h1:relay Skill Routing (no identity layer non-leader)=`new capability wanted \· └► mcp-tool-registry (register: screen w/ aegis's shared detection-classes) \· └► least-privilege-grants (who, how much — skill-line citation required) \· └► integration-patterns (reliability review before trial→active) \· └► egress-allowlist-authoring (derive + version + hand to quinn)` · h1:relay Skill Routing (no identity layer non-leader)=Handoffs out: scout (evaluation before registration) quinn (allowlist consumer, rail enforcement) aegis (security review method suspicious egress) gauge (failure/circuit signals) meta's fleet-governance (any change beyond registration bookkeeping Rail proposal). Precedence: registration before grants before integration before allowlist never skip forward; incident question outranks everything.